        "title": "docs: add Sakana AI provider detail page",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds `docs/sakana.md`, the provider reference page for Sakana AI. This fills a gap left after #1774 merged the Sakana provider implementation in June 2026.\n\nAll other active providers that ship with a settings UI have a detail page in `docs/`; Sakana AI was the only one missing. The page covers setup, the manual Cookie auth flow, data source, parsed quota windows (5-hour and weekly), CLI usage, error table, and related files.\n\n## Details\n\n- Fills the missing `docs/sakana.md` entry to match the pattern for other providers.\n- Content derived from `SakanaProviderDescriptor.swift`, `SakanaUsageFetcher.swift`, `SakanaSettingsReader.swift`, `SakanaProviderImplementation.swift`, and existing test fixtures.\n- No code, config, or runtime behavior changes; docs only.\n- PR #1783 (open) handles the `docs/providers.md` count update, strategy table row, and `## Sakana AI` section; a `Details:` link can be added there once both land.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node Scripts/check-documentation-links.mjs` — documentation links OK: 134 local links\n- `node Scripts/check-site-locales.mjs` — app/site locales OK\n- `node Scripts/generate-llms.mjs --check` — llms index OK\n- `node Scripts/check-app-locales.mjs --test` — locale tests OK\n- `bash Scripts/lint.sh lint-linux` — 0 violations, 0 serious in 1195 files\n- `git diff --check` — clean",
